ile amansz bir puan mcadelesine girebilirsiniz. "yeni oyunlar" sekmesi ile sitemize yklenen gncel oyunlar takip edebileceiniz gibi, isterseniz dier kullanclarn en ok ilgi gsterdii oyunlar iin "popler oyunlar" sekmesine, isterseniz de bilinmeyen bir maceraya atlmak iin "rastgele oyunlar" sekmesine tklayabilirsiniz. olumsuz ieriklerden tamamen arndrlarak uzmanlarmz tarafndan zel olarak hazrlanm sitemizde; 3d oyunlar, aksiyon oyunlar, araba oyunlar, basketbol oyunlar, beceri oyunlar, bisiklet oyunlar, izgi film oyunlar, ocuk oyunlar, dv oyunlar, futbol oyunlar, giydirme oyunlar, iki kiilik oyunlar, kz oyunlar, komik oyunlar, macera oyunlar, makyaj oyunlar, motor oyunlar, oda oyunlar, online oyunlar, sava oyunlar, silah oyunlar, spor oyunlar, yar oyunlar, yemek oyunlar, zeka oyunlar kategorilerimizden herhangi birine giri yaparak hemen oyun oynamaya balayabilirsiniz. oyun10.comda yer alan tm oyunlar reticisine aittir. sitemizde bulunan metin, grsel veya altyapsal dosyalarn eitli yollarla kopyalanmas veya izin almakszn kullanlmas yasaktr. bu tr bir olayla karlaldnda oyun10 ynetimi hukuki yollara bavurma hakkn sakl tutmaktadr. en gzel futbol oyunlar dier oyun sitemiz minioyun.org'da! :) ko fred ko 2

sciences continent sciences par stphane deligeorges le lundi de 16h  16h55 podcast s'abonner via itunes s'abonner via rss quel est le fondement de la dmarche scientifique, quels sont ses ressorts, ses motivations, quelle que soit la discipline : chaque semaine un entretien avec un chercheur diffrent. en savoir plus sur l'mission : continent sciences" comment commence-t-on et construit-on une carrire scientifique ? il existe un fond commun dans l'attitude scientifique.mais si l'on passe d'une discipline  l'autre, alors, qu'est-ce qui fait le spcifique d'un biologiste ?d'un spcialiste des volcans, d'un palontologue, ou d'un physicien thoricien ? tous ceux qui prcdent sont des dcouvreurs.mais il y a l'immense corps de ceux qui s'activent dans les applications de la science, qui prennent des brevets pour certains procds, conoivent les trains  grande vitesse, les fuses ou les plantes transgniques. quelles sont leurs opinions, leurs convictions sur les consquences sociales de leur travail ? continent sciences , chaque lundi, de 14h  15h pour comprendre les sciences  travers les femmes et les hommes qui les font. en partenariat avec les sciences, on en parle aussi sur : saison __label__low roger liebi hauptmen home curriculum vitae termine gstebuch links fragen & antworten impressum freundesbrief der freundesbrief wird ca. 8 mal pro jahr verschickt. email address * vornamen * nachnamen * suche suche downloads vortragsliste (1) glaubwrdigkeit (2) altes testament (81)at allgemein (6) at geschichtsbcher (16) at gesetz mose (13) at grosse propheten (25) at kleine propheten (16) at poetische bcher (9) biblische lehre (47)aktuelle themen (24) bibel (15) prophetie (4) heilsgeschichte (7) kirchengeschichte (2) neues testament (30)nt allgemein (6) nt allgemeine briefe (11) nt evangelien-apostelgeschichte (3) nt paulusbriefe (14) benutzeranmeldung benutzername * passwort * neues benutzerkonto erstellen benutzernamen vergessen neues passwort anfordern sie sind hierstartseite | biblische lehre prophetie wie kann man verbreitete irrtmer ber biblische prophetie vermeiden? 24. mrz 2015 15:15 | edne in einer zeit, in der es so wichtig wre, genau auf das prophetische wort als auf eine lampe, die an dunklem orte leuchtet, zu achten (2pet 1,19), wird durch falsche auslegungen ber prophetie enorm viel verwirrung gestiftet. so wird z.b. behauptet, die entrckung werde erst in der grossen drangsal stattfinden, der kommende antichrist sei der islam, das 1000-jhrige reich sei schon jetzt, als nchstes komme der angriff von gog und magog etc. wie kann man diese behauptungen biblisch widerlegen? wie kann man berhaupt zu klarheit und sicherheit in prophetischen dingen gelangen? dokument: verbreitete_irrtuemer_ueber_prophetie.pdf der messias im at und seine erwartung im judentum 9. juli 2013 11:59 | edne dokument: der_messias_des_at_und_seine_erwartung_im_judentum.pdf abriss der kommenden prophetischen ereignisse 9. juli 2013 10:36 | edne dokument: abriss_der_kommenden_prophetischen_ereignisse.pdf erfllte prophetie - gottes siegel auf die bibel 27. november 2012 01:49 | admin vor 2000 jahren wurde jesus in bethlehem geboren. durch sein kommen erfllte jesus christus ber 300 prophezeiungen aus dem alten testament, die den verheissenen erlser fr israel und alle vlker betrafen. es gibt nur zwei mglichkeiten: entweder war dies alles reiner zufall oder aber jesus christus ist tatschlich der von gott gesandte erretter. prfen sie selbst! wir nehmen 50 erfllte prophezeiungen unter die lupe und vergleichen sie mit den geschichtlichen tatsachen. ein spannendes unterfangen! dokument: abriss_der_kommenden_prophetischen_ereignisse.pdf aktuelle termine ch-zrich-rlikon: einfhrung in die apostelgeschichte (teil ii) 25.04.2018 20:00 - 21:30 veranstaltungsort: ehemalige friedhofkapelle christliche versammlung schwammendingerstrasse 69 8050-zrich-rlikon stichworte: vortrag ch-5027 herznach: bibelstudientag 28.04.2018 10:00 - 17:00 veranstaltungsort: gemeindehaus schulstrasse 9, 5027 herznach/ag stichworte: bibelstudientag ch-la chaux-de-fonds: parler en langues - que dit la bible? __label__low woodwright 2 go cabinets, doors, furniture, built-ins, trim work home page cabinets / kitchens furniture doors / gates little things design details houses contact little free library at louisville house houses - built and remodelled louisville house our current home is in old town louisville, co. weve been remodeling it for 18 years. the dramatic new porch designed by architect peter stewart was added in 2014. in 2011, we tore out the 8 high living room ceiling, creating a more expansive space. we changed the kitchen in 2004, and again in 2016. there is not a single square foot of this home that we havent remodeled in some way. louisville living room the commons house in 1992, we built this home at the commons on the alameda, a santa fe co-housing community. its passive solar with radiant heat floors. we used design elements from the nicolai fechin home in taos, nm as inspiration for interior details. this old photo was taken before the landscaping was done. today, its surrounded by beautiful, low-water plants. commons house living room lamy downs lamy downs is the little house we built in lamy, nm, outside of santa fe, in 1989. its heated by passive solar with interior adobe walls and a small wood stove for back-up. although built on a shoe-string budget, all the custom touches created a pleasing and cozy home. lamy downs interior view houses - portfolio samples louisville living room louisville dining room commons patio commons entry door commons kitchen lamy downs kitchen eric c. williams ericcw@earthlink.net 303-888-2868 contact web master  woodright 2 go 2009-2017

__label__low skip to content pantone 4c jeg elsker bare at blogge menu home links sitemap blog posted on april 11, 2018 by adminuse these tips to have fun with your blog many times a blog will focus on one topic. if you are passionate enough to write a blog about one topic, then this article offers plenty of valid advice for making that blog more efficient. use the information and tips contained in this article to help you learn more about creating a successful blog. if you are serious about blogging, buy a custom domain name rather than hosting your blog on a free service like blogger. it is fairly inexpensive to purchase your own name, and it will give you a more professional appearance. using your businesss name or something related to it will make it easier for viewers to remember it. a good way to get more traffic to your blog is by making comments on others blogs. google reader allows you to organize your blogs by folder. make a folder for the blogs you most want to follow so that you can find them when you want them. whenever you have the urge to say something, make a comment on them. your blog should be unique, so it stands out in the crowd. stick with interesting, unique content. providing information that is difficult for people to find will also draw readers. post content about a unique experience or hobby. give the intimate details of how a widget is constructed. this way, you give readers reasons to read your blog if they need certain information. frequently write in your blog. one of the biggest mistakes bloggers make is not updating the blog often enough. even if readers love your blog, theyll lose interest if they have to wait a long time for updates. a great idea is to make a new blog update weekly and update your readers by email. make use of images within your posts often. many people say that a picture is worth 1000 words. theres no better place to prove how much more pictures are worth to readers than within a blogthey are a vital part of your communication. image are capable of conveying much more than mere words. for this reason, you should include as many images as you can within your blog. update your site regularly. in order to keep your current subscribers visiting your blog, you need to keep giving them new content to read. regular new content will also help you to attract new visitors. if you neglect to add new articles to your blog, you will rapidly find that your readership decreses. try to aim for posting at least one time every day. allow occasional guest posts on your blog. this helps you build up connections with other bloggers, which is a helpful tool. do not disregard the importance of building cooperative relationships. you might need a favor in the future, and the blogger with whom youve been exchanging guest posts might be happy to help you. blog about topics that people want to know about. everyday chores like dusting and doing the laundry really arent so interesting. unless your blogs are unique when writing about common topics, people wont read it. pick a topic that you know will interest people. running a blog success, after all, relies on your ability to attract readers. post lots of new content on a regular basis, as this will keep readers hungry for more quality posts. the majority of the most successful blogs post a new entry at least once per day. if you think this may be difficult for you to achieve, put together advanced material that you can later add daily prior to the initial launch of your blog. this will mean that you still have some content to post even if you have a day when you cant write anything. be sure your blog offers something that is different from all others. readers will be attracted to unique information. posting difficult to find information will also do wonders for your blog. talk about unusual and interesting events and experiences. provide minute details about the way a widget is created. the idea is to provide readers with a reason to look for posts on your site. read all of your comment,s and try to respond to any feedback given without taking it too personally. people will always criticize you no matter what the topic is. if constructive criticism is posted, consider using it to make your blog better. for negative comments that are more destructive, leave a polite and brief response and dont look back. by being mature when dealing with commenters, youll get more respect from your readers and you may attract new readers. use images in your posts. you must have heard that a picture is worth 1000 words. it is certainly true in terms of writing a blog. image are capable of conveying much more than mere words. thus, it makes sense to supplement your posts with images whenever you can. when it comes to gaining traffic on your blog, you need to focus on providing interesting, informed and inspirational articles. readers will return if they think your articles are high quality and interesting. dont forget about the logistics. this means doing all the boring maintenance chores that needs to be done, as well as updating parts of your design from time to time. this will help readers from getting bored, and will also ensure that nobody has a problem visiting your blog. a topic that excites your interest and passion is particularly important when you make a blog. when you write about things you have a genuine interest in, your writing will be much better. this will translate well to your readers, increasing their commitment to return. mailing list remember to select effective keywords which are unique and less competitive. dont use common keywords that many bloggers are already using; theres too much competition for these keywords. itll be difficult for readers to find your blog if you use these keywords. be unique if you want to get the readers views. create a mailing list when you start your blog. if you create the list early enough, it will have ample time to grow. having a list of email addresses of those who have opted in to read your content can be useful for additional communication opportunities in the future. not beginning a mailing list early can be a huge mistake. the longer your posts are, the more you need to make sure that you are separating the article appropriately, and using subheadings. that will make your blog more readable, which will give you bigger readership. by utilizing this simple step, you boost your blogging skills to a higher level. dont just write a lot of content without a game plan. your articles need to be well researched and relevant to your target audience and keywords. if you dont put thought into what youre writing, your blog probably wont become successful. remember, the success of your blog is determined by the content you produce for it. your love and enjoyment of your blog is integral to its success. blogging can become boring, and thus be boring to readers if you arent passionate and involved in what you are writing. whatever topics you love, blog about them. blogging should be fun. stay creative, happy and upbeat, and your readers will reflect their enjoyment by sharing your content with others. it will make your blog have integrity if you stick to a schedule that is regular. there are new blogs going up all the time, and if you dont stay consistent with your postings, people might look to another blog. while you should feel free to take breaks around the holidays or other special occasions, frequent posting should be your goal. be certain you keep your keywords italicized and bolded. this will make the article pop, and also make search engines more likely to notice your site. if a keyword is unique, more readers will be intrigued and click on it. think about designing your blog posts using bullet lists, italics, bold text and other ways that will stand out within your blogging niche. this will make search engines rank your site higher and will increase views on your site. this piece of advice is quite powerful and can help you in a number of ways. create a dynamic and different kind of home page. on most blog sites, the homepage appears as a list of all the recent posts. try to make yours more interesting by customizing your homepage. this is particularly important because your blog will probably be discovered through search engines or links. when blogging, try not to keep things too simple. learn constantly, always research and think of this like its a business. learn from other seasoned bloggers, and incorporate different strategies and techniques that you pick up along the way. continuously improve and learn about new blogging methods that will help you move forward. use interlinks within the content of your blogs. this allows your readers to easily navigate your blog, keeping them happy. theres nothing worse than when you cant find what youre looking for on a confusing site. bolding and italicizing keywords can be helpful. this makes your keywords stand out to readers and search engines alike. setting your keywords apart from other text in this manner attracts peoples attention and makes them more likely to read your content. focus on other bloggers who are in your niche and make sure you are one step ahead. your blog is in competition with theirs, and its important that you know what theyre doing. also remember that while you are looking at their sites, there is a good chance that they are looking at yours. font size its important to understand the social side of blogging. the social nature of blogging requires that you interact with your readers on a regular basis. you also need to make contacts that write about the same topics that you do. success wont happen without work. the fortunes of your blog are dependent on your initiative. pay attention to the font size you choose for your blog. since written content is crucial on your blog, you need to be sure its font is readable. the right font size toes the fine line between being readable and being obnoxious; choose one that strikes the right balance. dont cram your blog full to the brim with keywords. choosing keywords selectively is crucial for your blog. however, quality is much more vital than quantity. search engines are much better at separating the wheat from the chaff than they were even five years ago. when you have too many keywords on your site, search engines will flag it and your rank in the search results pages will drop because it will be clear that quality isnt what you are concerned about. this is why you should select precise keywords that have been proven to increase your amount of traffic. commonly, ads are becoming a bigger part of blogs as people look to make money. however, you will probably have a hard time attracting readers if you have too many ads on your site. once they look at all of the ads, they will probably search for a less cluttered blog. posting videos to your site can give it a more appealing look. remember, however, that as great as videos are, solid written content is still priority number one. include text descriptions or even transcripts for every video that you post. this will help you generate key words that relate to your video, which helps people find your blog when searching the internet. think about whether or not you really need ads on your blog. advertisements are a common way for bloggers to make money. the problem with advertisements is that, well, they are advertisements. the fact that you are trying to make money becomes immediately obvious to the reader. having a lot of visual appeal in a blog can be helpful in attracting your audience. photos and colorful quotes will give readers interesting things to view. this is a great and easy way for you to get your readers more interested in your writings. make sure you incorporate visuals into your blog. graphs, photos of your family or even cartoons will increase the quality of each blog post. you will increase the interest of your readers in this manner. use backlinks effectively to increase search engine visibility and increase readers for your site. if search engines, like google, recognize your page as an authority, your website will rank higher. the more other websites and blogs link to your site, the more authoritative it will seem. this is known as back linking. be sure to get a variety of good backlinks, rather than having lots from one site. the above article offered lots of writing a blog information. if you are feeling a little overwhelmed right now, that is completely normal. even though it can be hard work, running a blog is well worth the effort. be sure to keep this article somewhere so that youre able to use it later. trade links to build more traffic for your website over time. trade links with bloggers who have sites about relevant information or topics to yours. dont waste your time or your readers time by trading links with sites that arent relevant to your own blog. if you focus your efforts on bringing quality traffic to your site, you will rank more highly in search engine results pages. blogger share this:click to share on twitter (opens in new window)click to share on facebook (opens in new window)click to share on google+ (opens in new window) related categoriesblog tagsfont size, list early, mailing list, search engines post navigation previous postprevious use social media to boost your marketing with these ideasnext postnext expert running a blog tips and tricks to get you started search for: search recent posts make social media marketing your oyster with our techniques fast advice to improve your blogging ability easy tips and tricks for better running a blog create an impact online: how to succeed at writing a blog try these social media marketing tips __label__low home how to be how to be happy alone  today  tomorrow  any day. blog on tv in your undies  keeping your word. slay your toxic noise barons how listening can give you more. taking the time to listen silence your negative thoughts the sound of silence what is enthusiasm anyway? nap your way to success random acts of enthusiasm wired for enthusiasm what can big bird, ernie and bert tell us about enthusiasm the enthusiasm of the celebrated pedestrian the way to your dreams. what is your mission in life homing in on the one goal weigh the positives and negatives for goal setting your shot at the stars  the importance of goals. use smart goals use your smart goals downloads the sound of silence april 14, 2017 ipdove silence 0 0sharessharetweet where we are: 2017  cycle 2  week 2: silence  day 5. when paul simon wrote the sound of silence when he was just 21 years old, he must have been in a melancholy mood. simon liked to play his guitar in the bathroom (because of the echo) and in darkness. he also liked to play like this with the tap running. so we can understand now what he meant by the lyrics: aloha darkness, my old friend. but wait a minute, there is noise here isnt there? the tap running for one. the guitar and its echo for another. but to simon they added to the silence  i think a bit like when some people gnaw on the end of a pencil or bite their lip if theyre concentrating on something. something there but not interfering. garfunkel once summed up the songs meaning as the inability of people to communicate with each other, not particularly internationally but especially emotionally, so what you see around you are people unable to love each other. as we have seen this week, true communication begins with listening  keep practicing to grow stronger and more confident and you will bring yourself closer to those you love and who love you. previousslay your toxic noise barons nextsilence your negative thoughts search for: free self mastery emails get daily tips in your inbox. we respect your privacy. categories enthusiasm keep your word order and planning silence pages be mindful blog downloads feeling disconnected? de febrero 2013 , 08:12 p.m. el director de la polica cuenta con menos de un mes para convocar a una rueda de prensa y rectificar una 'exclusiva' de hace 16 aos revelada por el desaparecido noticiero de televisin qap: la supuesta vinculacin de dos reconocidos empresarios a un cartel de narcos de buenaventura.la orden la dio el consejo de estado en una indita sentencia que condena a la nacin a una millonaria indemnizacin y a la rectificacin, que tendr que hacerse por los canales institucionales de televisin.el hecho ocurri el 23 de octubre de 1996, cuando qap (en su momento uno de los de mayor sintona) abri su emisin con la incautacin de 11 toneladas de cocana en la embarcacin celso, de bandera panamea, frente a playas de esmeraldas (ecuador). la operacin cont con el apoyo de las autoridades colombianas y la dea y permiti la captura de cinco colombianos.en el fallo, los magistrados reconstruyeron la presentacin de la noticia. sealan que luego de una breve exposicin de los presentadores una periodista entrevist al entonces subdirector de la polica, general luis enrique montenegro; al comandante de antinarcticos, coronel leonardo gallego, y al jefe de la dea en el pas, larry lions.segundos despus, en la pantalla aparecieron los nombres y apellidos de los supuestos responsables del embarque, entre ellos los dos empresarios. la informacin aseguraba que todos trabajaban a rdenes del capo vctor patio fmeque. el consejo de estado reconstruy todos los problemas financieros y econmicos derivados de la informacin, que al final termin siendo desvirtuada por la investigacin de la fiscala. "la informacin de los organismos de inteligencia de la polica nacional fue liberada, manipulada y entregada indebidamente, contraviniendo por completo los postulados de la reserva de las informaciones que tiene bajo su custodia y estudio", sealaron los magistrados. y agregan que "filtrar datos inexactos viola la libertad de prensa". la sentencia tambin deja en claro que no existe "reparo alguno" sobre la forma como el noticiero qap obtuvo la noticia ni como la difundi. en el proceso se encontr que los organismos de inteligencia de la polica apenas estaban recaudando informacin y an no haban verificado la veracidad de los datos ni la plena identidad de los supuestos responsables del cargamento ilegal. con reservas, procurador puede conocer actas sobre demanda de nicaragua la sala de consulta del consejo de estado le dijo al gobierno que puede entregarle a la procuradura copia de las actas de las sesiones de la comisin asesora de relaciones exteriores en las que se discuti la demanda de nicaragua sobre aguas territoriales en el caribe. esa fue la respuesta, que no obliga, a una consulta de la cancillera sobre la peticin que hizo el ministerio pblico, que a la vez indaga eventuales responsabilida- des en la estrategia de defensa que termin con el fallo adverso en la haya.la sala advierte que el procurador puede tener acceso a las actas, pero que est obligado a guardar la reserva sobre esos documentos. "mientras (la reserva) no sea levantada por el presidente de la repblica y la comisin asesora de relaciones exteriores, el procurador no las podr revelar", dice el concepto. el artculo 4 de la ley 68 de 1993, que fue tenido en cuenta por los magistrados, seala que la comisin asesora y el presidente de la repblica pueden decidir el levantamiento de la reserva. redaccin justicia comentar guardar ingrese o regstrese ac para guardar los artculos en su zona de usuario y leerlos cuando quiera este artculo ya fue guardado para consultarlo en otro momento, visite su zona de usuario. artculo guardado para consultarlo en otro momento, visite su zona de usuario. el artculo no pudo ser guardado, intente nuevamente reportar volver a portada sabemos que te gusta estar siempre informado. crea una cuenta y podrs disfrutar de: acceso a boletines con las mejores noticias de actualidad. comentar las noticias que te interesan. guardar tus artculos favoritos. crea una cuenta y podrs disfrutar nuestro contenido desde cualquier dispositivo. copyright  2018 el tiempo casa editorial. prohibida su reproduccin total o parcial, as como su traduccin a cualquier idioma sin autorizacin escrita de su titular. eltiempo.com todas las noticias principales de colombia y el mundo sguenos en:

__label__low vi bruger cookies til at huske dine indstillinger og give dig den bedst mulige oplevelse p sitet. nyheder 112 sport livsstil tv videnskab sex underholdning oversigt kronprinsens tur over storebltsbroen suser verden rundt nyheder skrevet af administrator | 13.01.15 | 08:47 12.01.15 / 13:59 del p facebook det har vakt opsigt internationalt, at kronprins frederik i weekenden tog turen over storebltsbroen, selvom den var lukket p grund af storm. europiske medier som bbc og det franske nyhedsbureau afp har begge sendt nyheden videre. derudover er historien net til kronprinsesse marys hjemland, hvor det australske nyhedsbureau aap har rapporteret om den royale kretur. samtlige medier har ogs videregivet hoffets undskyldning p vegne af kronprins frederik. iflge sund og blt, selskabet bag storebltsbroen, var det "grnsende til livsfarligt" at kre over broen, mens den var lukket p grund af den kraftige storm egon, der ramte danmark i weekenden. - det var en forkert beslutning at tage imod muligheden for, at bilen kunne fortstte, og det beklager kronprinsen, ld det mandag fra lene balleby, der er kommunikations- og pressechef for kongehuset. - kronprinsen er ked af det skete og kan godt forst, at situationen var med til at skabe yderligere frustrationer og vrede blandt de mennesker, der havde ventet i mange timer p at passere broen, sagde hun. ogs politiets efterretningstjeneste, pet, har beklaget, at kronprins frederik efterfulgt af livvagter krydsede en lukket storebltsbro, og pet gennemgr nu proceduren. stormen egon bragte lrdag vindstd op til orkanstyrke, hvilket lammede trafikken flere steder i danmark og lukkede storebltsbroen. det betd lange ventetider, da broen blev lukket lrdag omkring klokken 14 og frst bnede klokken fire natten til sndag. men kronprinsens bil krte over klokken 15.15 p vej mod herning og retur klokken 02.53, mens flere hundrede mennesker angiveligt mtte vente p, at broen bnede igen. /ritzau/ del p facebook twitter e-mail linse raser efter grsdagens afsnit af familien fra bryggen: totalt til grin! 24-rig kvinde voldtaget p offentligt toilet - __label__low the campaign for da home comment policy my burn policy 8.15.2011 random monday morning thoughts well, now i'm no so bummed about the 100 degree record falling on thursday when that fluke thunderstorm came through. saturday would have killed it any way. i don't know if much will be made of it, but the government in san francisco shutting down some cellphone towers to prevent the organization of protests should bother you greatly. cue the "what is this? communist russia?" theme. espn had a lot of little league games on this weekend. i think the kids are getting cockier with each passing year. michelle bachman wins the iowa straw poll, sarah palin shows up in iowa just to sign autographs and say "aw, shucks", and rick perry joins the race. i bet the president obama haters couldn't turn off cspan this weekend. an age that surprised me: michelle bachman is 55. that's a hot 55. an age that surprised me #2: al sharpton is 56. i would have thought he was in his 70s. did you know that a third grader is capable of telling a very long story and then, without missing a beat, tell the same very long story over again when her momma enters the room? idiocracy: there's a kids' game named "doggie doo". (thanks, thomas.) still no results in the search for the owner of the stray dog. we've put up posters as well as a listing on craig's list without luck. did i mention that he'd been neutered? and i gave him a bath this weekend. i think mrs. ll is distancing from the doggie. hey, i'm no pr expert, but if i'm a dallas cop who gets arrested outside of a strip club, i don't think i'd have a strip club picture as my facebook profile pic. you always see a pretty big turnout whenever a firefighter is killed regardless of the cause of death. (i.e. the guy that fell out of the stands at the rangers game.) it'll be interesting to see the response to the funeral of the dallas firefighter this weekend who actually died while fighting a fire. the dallas cowboys defense from last thursday night: a pic showing 14 men on the field. not much in the update today but i still get to be bothered by the death of a 32 year old from chico and a 43 year old from bridgeport. edit: motorcycle death. at 8:31 am email thisblogthis!share to twittershare to facebookshare to pinterest 50 comments: anonymous said... i'm glad you could get the update. i __label__low skip to content rtsoft wiki user tools log in site tools search toolsshow pagesourceold revisionsbacklinksrecent changesmedia managersitemaplog in> recent changesmedia managersitemap trace:  filemanager proton:filemanager table of contents file handling loading a file into memory base directory vs the user data directory using filemanager directly how to stream a file in mounting a .zip as a filesystem what about writing user data files? file handling first, you can use your good old c fwrite/fread or streams to your heart's content. but there is a reason why you shouldn't - the android file system sort of requires you to load your stuff from a giant zip, and using the filemanager instead hides this ugliness from you. loading a file into memory load any kind of file into memory like this: fileinstance myfile("test.txt"); //a small text file of 5 lines or so logmsg("i just loaded a file into memory that is %d bytes.", myfile.getsize()); logmsg(myfile.getaschars()); that list thing where i display the text file to the output window is only possible because of two things: i know it's a text file i know the filemanager secretly adds a null at the end when allocating memory for the file when the fileinstance object is destroyed as it goes out of scope, it deletes the associated memory it had loaded the file into. base directory vs the user data directory internally, fileinstance and functions like fileexists() are using the filemanager. the filemanager does the following for you behind the scenes: * automatically decompresses files that have been compressed with rtpack (file extension doesn't matter, it checks for a header) * automatically decompresses from a mounted .zip file when appropriate (the asset dir of the .apk in android is automatically mounted for you at init) * adds the base path of your app data, so interface/some.rtfont will work on all platforms (it prepends getbaseapppath() for you if needed) there are times when you don't want it to add the base path though, for instance, when saving user data, you should use getsavepath(). here is how we would have loaded the above from the user data directory: fileinstance myfile(getsavepath()+"test.txt", false); that false we send for the bool baddbasepath parm says don't prepend anything to the path, i know what i'm doing. it's available when using most file operations. using filemanager directly instead of using fileinstance, you could just do: int filesizebytes; byte *pdata = getfilemanager()->get(getsavepath()+"test.txt", &filesizebytes, true); //operate on data //we have to release the data ourselves or hello memory leak safe_delete_array(pdata); how to stream a file in to insure a hassle free android compile you should use filemanager::getstreaming instead of raw fopen/fread type stuff. it returns a streaminginstance that operates sort of like a fileinstance but actually smartly loads the file as you go, which may even be from a .zip file. why would you want to do this and not just load it all in one chunk? dungeon scroll's word dictionary is over one meg in size. streaming it means i can load 10kb at a time and update a progress bar each frame. example: int size; m_pstreaminginstance = getfilemanager()->getstreaming("some file", &size, false); //m_pstreaminginstance will be null on error //we now have a streaming instance, but we haven't actually loaded any data yet. we'll load directory into our own buffer. char st_buffer[4096]; while (m_pstreaminginstance->readlineoftext(st_buffer, 4096)) { logmsg(st_buffer); } safe_delete(m_pstreaminginstance); notice: we used streaminginstance::readlineoftext but we could have used streaminginstance::read instead for pure data. (it's a lot like fread) it internally cached the file for speed, for instance, if it's actually in a compressed zip and you are asking for one byte at a time it will really be decoding in 4 kb chunks behind the scenes mounting a .zip as a filesystem this happens automatically when you are doing an android target, so you can load resources by filename and not worry about where they actually are. (android wants to keep them in your .apk you used to install) but you may want to mount your own zips for some reason. let's examine how it's done: filesystemzip *pfilesystem = new filesystemzip(); pfilesystem->init("somezip.file")); //i'm not doing error handling in these examples, but it would return false on error //to print out the entire contents of the zip: vector contents = pfilesystem->getcontents(); for (int i=0; i setrootdirectory("assets"); //mount the assets directory only, the user won't have to have "assets" in the filename to find things in it //to actually mount it getfilemanager()->mountfilesystem(pfilesystem); //test that it worked: fileinstance myfile("textfileinsideassetsdirofthezip.txt"); if (myfile.isloaded()) logmsg("marty, it worked!"); what about writing user data files? i just use fwrite and fread and haven't have any trouble with porting so far. as long as you use getsavepath() you're ok as far as file permissions go. proton/filemanager.txt  last modified: 2012/03/09 01:05 by seth page tools show pagesourceold revisionsbacklinksback to top except where otherwise noted, content on this wiki is licensed under the following license: cc attribution-share alike 4.0 international

__label__low stel een vraag startpagina oplossingen en welkom bij de karify helpdesk voor clinten voer hier je zoekterm in.. zoeken maak je als zorgverlener gebruik van karify? ga dan naar de support pagina's startpagina oplossing help berichten hoe verstuur ik een bericht? gewijzigd op: do, 8 dec, 2016 at 2:32 pm met berichten in karify kun je in een veilige omgeving berichten versturen en ontvangen. ook kun je bestanden meesturen. maar hoe verstuur ik nou eigenlijk een bericht? ga via de navigatiebalk naar berichten: klik op de knop nieuw bericht rechtsboven in beeld: nu kun je een nieuw bericht typen. kies uit je contactlijst n of meerdere geadresseerden. ontvangers van het bericht zien altijd wie het bericht nog meer kunnen zien. zo weet je altijd wie de ontvangers zijn als je antwoordt. kies een kort en bondig onderwerp zodat de ontvanger direct weet waar het over gaat. in het tekstveld typ je je bericht. je hebt de mogelijkheid een bijlage aan je bericht toe te voegen. dit kan onderaan bij bijlage - voeg toe. zorg ervoor dat je in de begeleidende tekst duidelijk maakt wat je als bijlage meestuurt. was dit antwoord nuttig? ja nee hoe kunnen we dit artikel verbeteren? meer artikelen in berichten hoe verstuur ik een bericht? naar wie kan ik berichten versturen? bijlagen versturen en ontvangen mappen & favoriet e-consult afwezigheidsmelding karify 2017 algemene voorwaarden privacy en cookies
__label__low whatbreesees skip to content homebree upcoming shows past shows venues my jams friends with blogs tag archives: justin vernon december 26, 2017  9:16 pm bon iver friday, december 8, 2017 state theatre, portland, maine in a sentencefor me, sadly, this show was a surprising disappointment. i saw bon iver for the first time in september of 2012 at the bank of america pavillion in boston. caroline and i went together, and she wrote a lovely guest post giving the show a five star rating. i was in the third or fourth row for that full band show, and i was over the moon to hear some of my bon iver favorites in person and to sing the wolves (acts i and ii) together. the energy at that show was palpably positive. when i saw that bon iver was playing so nearby in portland at state theatre, i was thrilled. i set an alarm to buy tickets in the presale, but the timing of my teaching plans were a little off because we had an unexpected fire drill, so i selfishly asked my students to work on their homework for a few minutes while i tried to get tickets on both my laptop and my phone. my phone came through for me and i snagged a pair of tickets a few rows from the back of the room, and i cant think of a time i was so happy to have basically back row seats. i checked again when tickets went on sale to the general public, but they seemed completely sold out right away. i read through more than a hundred comments from angry bon iver fans about how impossible it was to get tickets for the show, and revelled in my luck. i even looked online at stubhub just to see if i could get seats closer to the stage, but seats in my far away section were selling for $250 each (a huge markup over the $65 face value). i scoffed at the idea of selling my tickets for profit anyhow, but then i went to the show and thought twice. bartlett was my lucky date for the night, even though many people inquired about my extra ticket for the show right up until the night of the show. we met for dinner at el rayo, had a couple of tacos and cocktails, and made our way to state theatreearly to make it through their added security and because there was no opening act. justin vernon took the stage solo, which i am usually totally in favor of, but this was an odd night. i was surprised by how many people were back and forth to the bar and bathroom during the show because wed all paid a decent amount for these highly sought after tickets and i figured everyone there would be a big fan. (a sarcastic shout out to the annoying super fan couple in the third row that spent most of the night dancing wildly on your feetrudely obstructing the views of and distracting everyone all around you. you guys made me glad my seats were so far away). there was some sort of chatter coming from the other front orchestra section, i guess, because justin interjected a snarky comment about them, and then followed up with a comment about how we should all just love each other. later, someone from the crowd shouted out i love you, justin, and he responded i have plans later. but i appreciate that. i thought some (but not all) of his banter with the audience was awkward to the point of kind of mean spirited. it felt like he didnt want to have to perform for us, and it ruined the show experience for me. my view of justin vernon from the back of the state theatre i didnt feel at all this way five years ago when i first saw bon iver live, so i have some theories about this nights cringeworthy moments. the easiest explanation would be that folks nearest him were being rude and i couldnt hear it. that, sadly, has been the case at other shows ive been to in portland, where people talk all night over the performer. regina spektors show earlier this year at state theatrecomes right to mind. maybe something has shifted for justin during these years that makes performing difficult for him, or, he was just having a bad night. if i missed something, please tell me. id love to know there was an obvious cause for his somewhat grumpy demeanor. musically, justin was great. i loved hearing so many songs i love liveflume,perth,blood bank,skinny love,and woodsand his cover ofi cant make you love mewas heart wrenching, as expected. i enjoyed hearing the heavily electronic songs from his 2016 album, 22, a million in person, too. it felt good to sing the wolves (acts i and ii) together to end the night at justins invitation, but i was very surprised he only played a one song encore (a cover of mahalia jacksons satisfied mind), because he was on stage less than an hour. id felt so lucky to have the opportunity to be in the room, but was genuinely sadly disappointed during and after the show. it felt like an off night from start to finish, and it seemed to me like justin struggles with the pressures of being a beloved musician, which seemed to shine through during this show. in the end, i am fine with having spent $65 to see justin vernon from basically the back row, but i probably wouldnt do it again, which is disappointing given how much his music has positively impacted my life. if you missed this show, i honestly dont think you missed much. maybe something was going on with the crowd up front that i couldnt hear. if folks were being rude and justin was annoyed with themi can totally live with that. from where i sat, though, this show was a bummer. if you saw another night of this tour and had a very positive experience, i would also like to hear from you so that i know this was simply an off night and that justin is just fine. im truly hoping for that. xo, bree advertisements leave a comment filed under uncategorized tagged as bon iver, el __label__low dialogue-abrahaml'quipe de "dialogue abraham" vous souhaite la bienvenue ! ce forum recherche avant tout une atmosphre cordiale et respectueuse, chacun s'efforant d'couter l'autre avec la mme bienveillance qui doit accueillir son propre tmoignage. nous travaillons  nous comprendre mutuellement en vrit, et non  entretenir des conflits. nous ne sommes pas parfaits, mais pensons qu'il est possible d'avoir des changes de qualit sur les sujets religieux. puissiez-vous, vous qui venez ici, contribuer  cet effortdialogue-abrahamforum interreligieux du blog collectif judo-islamo-chrtien cr le 10 fvrier 2011accueil faq s'enregistrer connexion avertissement : les "sujets similaires" suggrs en bas de chaque discussion lorsque vous n'tes pas connects ne sont pas de notre responsabilit. il en va de mme pour les publicits qui peuvent apparatre sous ce message. ces messages automatiss sont gnrs par notre hbergeur sans aucun contrle de notre part. ils peuvent donc prsenter des opinions opposes  nos valeurs et  celles des religions et philosophies reprsentes sur cet espace d'change et de fraternit. merci de votre comprhension.musique et religiondialogue-abraham :: gnral :: dbats gnrauxpage 2 sur 4  partagez  page 2 sur 4  1, 2, 3, 4 re: musique et religion gilbert-michel le mer 18 mai - michigan - jose's authentic mexican restaurant united states michigan (mi) emmet county petoskey petoskey restaurants jose's authentic mexican restaurant mexican in n. michigan review of jose's authentic mexican restaurant 21 photos jose's authentic mexican restaurant 309 petoskey st, petoskey, mi 49770-2425 +1 231-348-3299 improve this listing ranked #30 of 107 restaurants in petoskey 102 reviews cuisines: mexican restaurant details drcheesela junta, colorado14346reviewed july 19, 2012 mexican in n. michiganwhen in petoskey i go to jose's. the food is fresh, especially the pico de gallo and guacamole. they have the best chile rellenos in the state as far as i'm concerned (unless you make them homemade). the place is casual and the staff friendly. i don't give it an "excellent" because while the food is worth the price you have to pay extra for chips. i think free salsa & chips isn't too much to ask for. but...i'll keep going back!valueatmosphereservicefoodask drcheese about __label__low see all stores cars for sale sell your car financing articles 7 best small trucks for 2018 best-selling cars 7 best small trucks for 2018 published friday, april 13, 2018 01 the right combination of ruggedness and style. a pickup truck is a practical vehicle option for many drivers. at the same time, larger pickup trucks can sometimes be a little "over-the-top" for basic hauling, towing, and cargo needs. this is where shopping for small pickup trucks can be a wise option. with a smaller sized or midsize pickup truck, you can still enjoy substantial towing capacity and cargo storagealong with greater fuel economy and maneuverability in even the smallest of urban spaces. in many ways, small pickup trucks offer the best of both worlds! looking for some help in narrowing down your options when it comes to a small truck purchase? we've already taken care of some of the research for you. this list of seven top small trucks was developed based on vehicle type and carmax sales data from september 29, 2017 through march 29, 2018. here are our findings: ford explorer sport trac honda ridgeline ford ranger gmc canyon chevrolet colorado nissan frontier toyota tacoma 07 ford explorer sport trac first created in 2001 as an offshoot of the popular ford explorer suv, the ford explorer sport trac is similar in body style to the explorer suv with the addition of a small pickup bed in the back. and while this particular vehicle was only manufactured until 2010 (with a year off in 2006), it reached peak popularity in the small truck market due to its innovation (especially for its time) and functionality. if you're feeling a little torn between an suv and a pickup truck for your next vehicle, the sport trac might be a good compromise for you. and despite the fact that it hasn't been in production in awhile, you can generally still find used sport tracs on the market, particularly in the 2007 through 2010 model years. 06 honda ridgeline if you're intrigued by the idea of an suv/pickup crossover but are looking for something with more recent production, the honda ridgeline is definitely worth a test drive. the 2017 version of this vehicle boasts a unique two-way tailgate that is even wider and longer than that of most midsize pickup trucks. it also comes standard with a powerful 3.5 liter v6 engine, though upgraded engine options are available as you move up in trim level. speaking of trim options, the 2017 ridgeline is available in an impressive range of seven trims, including the base rt, sport, rtl-e, and premium black edition. standard features across all trim levels include a rearview camera, tow hitch, and 18-inch wheels. 05 ford ranger originally manufactured from 1983 through 2011, the ford ranger consistently topped lists for best-selling small pickup trucks. in 2019, ford will bring back the ranger with a brand new redesign that many are eagerly anticipating. in the meantime, you can still find used ford rangers on the market, such as the popular 2011 ranger. this small pickup truck is available in both a regular and extended cab, known as the supercab, for additional passenger leg room. the 2011 ranger also comes in both a six-foot and seven-foot bed option to suit your hauling needs, and is available in three trim levels: the xl, xlt, and sport. a 2.3 liter, 143-horsepower engine comes standard, though an upgraded v6 is an option on the xlt and sport trims. 04 gmc canyon looking for a pickup truck with a little more cabin space than some of these smaller pickups on the market? if so, then the gmc canyon is a great midsize pickup option worth your consideration. the 2017 version of this truck is available in your choice of two-, four-, or -five-seater options, as well as two different bed lengths and five trim options to choose from: the base sl, canyon, sle, slt, and premium denali. standard features across all trim levels include a 2.5 liter, four cylinder engine, rearview camera, and 4.2-inch color display. and in its upgraded v6 engine, you'll enjoy a maximum towing capacity of 7,000 pounds (versus 3,500 pounds with the standard engine). 03 chevrolet colorado another excellent midsize pickup truck to consider is the chevrolet colorado. this truck has been one of the best-selling pickups on the market for many years, and for good reason. the 2017 colorado boasts impressive maneuverability and handling, especially when compared to its full-size counterpart (the silverado). it is also available with a wide range of customization options that buyers will love, including three engine choices, several different bed configurations, two bed lengths, and a whopping five trim levels. in the base trim, drivers will enjoy an extended cab, rearview camera, and 2.5 liter engine. upgrade to the lt trim, however, and you'll also enjoy an available 4g wi-fi hot spot! 02 nissan frontier when it comes to midsize pickup trucks that are both practical and affordable, the nissan frontier is a strong contender. while it may not be loaded with standard features, the 2017 frontier is a rugged work truck that will serve many drivers well. offered in both a crew cab and extended cab, as well as a 5-foot or 6.1-foot bed length, this frontier comes in your choice of five trim levels. standard on the base s trim are rear privacy glass, bluetooth connectivity, and 15-inch wheels. in order to upgrade from the base four cylinder engine (and 3,500-pound towing capacity, when properly equipped1), however, you'll need to select the sv or higher trim (which comes with a v6 capable of towing nearly double that when the vehicle is properly equipped). 01 toyota tacoma topping our list of best small pickup trucks is the toyota tacoma. looking at the 2017 tacoma, drivers love its high profile and abundant standard features, which include a durable composite bed (no liner needed!), a backup camera, and even a built-in gopro mount on the windshield for easy recording. these ample features, combined with its towing capacity of nearly 7,000 pounds (when properly equipped1) and incredibly smooth ride, make the tacoma a top-seller in smaller pickups. false true new arrival shop used small trucks near you start your search __label__low mumblings from 203cm above earth this is the blog of steve davis. that is all. tuesday, january 24, 2006 much better day today was a much better day overall with much lower levels of anxiety and depression. i had a call back from the nlp practitioner and will arrange to do a course of 5 evening sessions with her at the end of february. she's convinced that nlp will definately help. i have to admit to being a little sceptical but will give anything a go. oh my god! i decided to try something different at the gym today and had a go at a body combat class. i'm not sure what i was expecting, perhaps a cross between martial arts and music but it was way more intense than anything i could have prepared for. it combined a very high energy dance workout with martial arts and combat moves, punches and kicks. it uses a completely different set of muscles than spinning and highlighted to me how little co-ordination i have. it took a little while to get into the flow and more often than not i was completely out of sync with everyone else but after about 20 minutes i got into the flow. i'll definately give it another go. i think i'm going to feel it tomorrow though :-) posted by steve at 21:29 no comments: post a comment newer post older post home subscribe to: post comments (atom) 1000 miles in 2012 this work is licensed under a creative commons attribution-noncommercial-no derivative works 3.0 license. my links garans blog my ebay auctions my flickr photos www.flickr.com this is a flickr badge showing public photos from stevedavis. make your own badge here. post labels blog car comments computers diet entertainment fun motorbike personal photos rants reviews travel work blog archive  2012 (4)  april (1)  january (3)  2010 (3)  june (1)  may (2)  2009 (14)  december (1)  november (1)  september (1)  june (2)  march (1)  february (3)  january (5)  2008 (90)  december (4)  november (3)  october (9)  september (10)  august (6)  july (14)  june (6)  may (16)  april (6)  march (9)  february (3)  january (4)  2007 (58)  december (2)  november (4)  october (2)  september (10)  august (4)  july (6)  june (2)  may (6)  april (3)  march (12)  february (4)  january (3)  2006 (62)  december (3)  november (2)  october (2)  september (1)  august (5)  july (4)  june (5)  may (5)  april (5)  march (10)  february (5)  january (15) at last! search! with over 350 materials and 100,000+ listings, we maintain one of north america's most extensive recycling databases.simply dial 1-800-cleanup, or simply enter in the material you are trying to recycle along with your zip code and click search. at earth911, weve created a community that helps consumers find their own shade of green, match their values to their purchase behaviors, adopt environmentally sound practices and drive impactful environmental changes. we are here to deliver a mix of targeted content and eco-conscious products that influence positive environmental actions so __label__low becoming what we already are a weblog about faith, life and stuff menu skip to content 12 apr 200912 apr 2009 pdbb now what? what's next? where shall we boldly go?? the title of todays posting now what? is a very good question being as this is still easter. in fact, just a little fyi for ya here easter lasts 50 daysup to pentecost. this not a season in the church year, like sundays in advent or what have you we have 50 days of easter. do you think you can make your left over ham and jelly beans stretch that far? seriously, i asknow what? because i started this blog as an exercise to go along with devotions about 60 of us at st. john did during lent. my question to you if you are in fact reading this is now what? i think i have gotten in to a groove with this and i think i will continue. that being said i would love to hear from you about what you would like to see here. if you have questions we could pursue together, or directions or topics we might explore i would love to hear about them. leave a comment and let me know wont ya? one final whats next? christians confess that jesus is our risen lord, so now that christ is raised whats next? maybe a fair question for us to ask ourselves each day! easter blessings. christ has risen! he has risen indeed! alleluia! advertisements share this:facebookgoogletwittertumblrpinterestemaillinkedinmoreprintredditlike this:like loading... related uncategorized published by pdbb just a guy who loves his callings in life as a father, husband, lutheran pastor and geek, nerd, or techno-whatever.. take a look at the gravatar, it is um... nearly spot on which is just a little spooky. view all posts by pdbb post navigation previous easternext gobsmacked leave a reply cancel reply enter your comment here... fill in your details below or click an icon to log in: email (required) (address never made public) name (required) website you are commenting using your wordpress.com account. __label__low pilotepro.fr - aventure d'un pilote franais au qubec bonjour  tous(tes). vous pouvez lire sur ce blog mon histoire raconte jours aprs jours durant ma vie au qubec, ainsi que des photos et vidos de mes vols durant ma formation de pilote. ceci me permet de vous prsenter pas  pas mon volution, et de vous faire partager mon mtier et ma passion: l'aviation transport canada and faa cpl/me/ir/fi atpl jaa russi 1200h total, 1050h pic, 700h fi home ajouter  mes favoris. me contacter niagara falls tour 2 sept-les spotting 1er solo test en vol cpl test en vol ifr qubec 10 mdvac ma rgion la gaspsie samedi 14 novembre 2009 un vol particulier... il y a quelques semaines une famille appelle ma compagnie pour faire un "vol coqueluche". mais qu'est-ce donc ?la coqueluche est une maladie trs contagieuse due  une bactrie du nom de bordetella pertussis (incroyable les recherches que l'on peut faire sur le net !). elle se caractrise par de violentes quintes de toux suivies dune respiration difficile appele  chant du coq .le  vol de coqueluche  ou  mthode strasbourgeoise  a t invent dans la premire moiti du xxe sicle par le docteur matter pour soigner la coqueluche.son principe est le suivant : monter le plus rapidement possible entre 9500 pieds et 11 500 pieds d'altitude dans un avion non pressuris, y rester une cinquantaine de minutes, redescendre aussi rapidement que possible, en respectant un palier  5000 pieds.pourquoi, en avion non pressuris, les malades retrouvaient-ils leur vitalit ?qui dit  brutale ascension  dit  rarfaction de loxygne , ce qui entrane un changement de pression au niveau du sang. les molcules doxyhmoglobine (qui a ?), transporteuses de loxygne dans le sang, relchent cet lment en plus grande quantit qu lordinaire. cette libration accrue doxygne a des consquences trs positives sur la vitalit.ce procd permet, non pas davoir plus doxygne, ce qui serait dangereux, mais dutiliser au mieux loxygne de lair naturellement disponible, sans danger et sans effets secondaires.cette technique optimise laction des mdicaments et lutte contre leur possible effets secondaires.j'ai donc fait ce vol pour le moins trange  premire vu, mais qui finalement a peut-tre guri cette mre et ces 3 enfants gs d'environ 4 ans. (n'ayant pas eut de retour je suppose qu'ils vont mieux :))on se serait cru dans un pisode de dr. house, mes passagers et moi-mmes ayant des masques mdicaux striles, lgrement effrayant pour les enfants, en pleur durant la totalit du vol !le vol a t plutt plaisant pour moi, en c-182rg turbo, la monte  11 500 pieds s'est faite en 10 minutes environ, une altitude o je n'ai pas le droit d'y rester plus de 30min sans apport d'oxygne supplmentaire. j'ai du redescendre quelques instants  9 500' avant d'y remonter pour une vingtaine de minutes encore.quant  la descente qui doit tre rapide... elle l'a t !environ 4000' / minutes, au grand "non-bonheur" des oreilles de mes passagers malades, pour qui j'ai du ralentir cette descente !en tout cas, cette journe l restera une exprience parmi les autres, et  11 500' l'air est pur, et tout parait petit, surtout les hommes... publi par juju  23:47 3 commentaires articles plus rcents articles plus anciens accueil inscription  : articles (atom) qui suis-je ? julien, n  nice, pilote professionnel, instructeur de vol tcca et faacpl/ir/fi/me/atpl ambiance... mon logbook au 17/03/2010 mes rcits ...  2011 (1)  aot (1)  2010 (3)  octobre (1)  mars (1)  fvrier (1)  2009 (15)  novembre (1) un vol particulier...  septembre (2)  juillet (2)  juin (2)  mai (2)  avril (3)  mars (2)  fvrier (1)  2008 (53)  dcembre (4)  novembre (5)  octobre (5)  septembre (4)  aot (5)  juillet (5)  juin (5)  mai (5)  avril (5)  mars (4)  fvrier (5)  janvier (1)  2007 (36)  dcembre (2)  novembre (5)  octobre (7)  septembre (1)  aot (3)  juillet (2)  mai (3)  avril (1)  mars (4)  fvrier (4)  janvier (4) photo du jour mes liens favoris rollinks transfers au pays de l'azur... blog de steve danny's news... le blog de fabien le blog de jj le blog de mon ami tributaire :-) le meilleur de l'aviation suivre par email :-) visiteurs ... compteur

__label__low search this site: home eligibility  application process services   sf access  taxi & ramp taxi service  shop-a-round rules & policies fare information   sf access  taxi & ramp taxi service  shop-a-round resources news employment opportunities contact us  sf accesssf access fare informationfares sf access service costs a certified rider $2.50 per one-way trip. all riders are required to pay the driver either in cash (exact change please) or with a single ride ticket that costs $2.50 each and may be purchased from the san francisco paratransit office in whatever quantity needed. these ride tickets do not expire. when purchasing sf access ride tickets by mail, please allow sufficient time to receive the tickets. sf access fares must be paid upon boarding and are subject to change. companions as a certified rider, you may arrange to bring one (1) companion or guest with you on each ride for $2.50 per ride, per companion. fares for companions may also be paid using ride tickets available from the san francisco paratransit office. you may add additional fare paying companions to your trip only on a same day, space available basis. please check with your provider on the day of service whether these arrangements can be made. you will need to verify that there is space available on both trips if you would like the addtional companions to accompany you on a round trip. attendants an attendant is someone who provides assistance you need in order to complete the requested trip or at your destination. typically, an attendant provides specialized assistance that the driver is unable to provide or assists the rider with activities of daily living at the destination. if you have been certified as needing an attendant, the attendant may ride with you at no additional charge. the attendant can ride in addition to any companion you may be taking. both attendants and companions must start and end their travel at the same address as the certified rider. some content on this page is saved in an alternative format, adobe acrobat. to view these files, download the following free software: adobe reader home page  services  sf access  taxi ramp taxi services  shop-a-round  fare informationabout us  resources  contact us  news page  doing business with sf paratransit  partnerstemplate_fare-info-sfaccess.php

driving related question: * leave this field blank: free dmv practice tests > 6 high way driving tips for new drivers the daily driver / blog 6 high way driving tips for new drivers 1. pay careful attention to the speed limit ever drive down the highway, only to see a vehicle that is moving at a ridiculously slow speed such as 40mph? what they are doing is illegal on many highways, as there is usually a minimum speed of 45mph required on such highways. driving too slowly poses a hazard not only to you, but also to everyone else using that highway. plus, it's annoying to everyone, and you could be ticketed for it. on the other hand, the speed limit on most highways is 70mph during the day, and 65mph during the night. once again, the speed limit varies from highway to highway, as there are some that don't get very much traffic at all, and therefore the limit is slightly increased for these places. 2. stay in the right lane keep a close eye on any signs that may read "left lane for passing only", as these are especially common in states such as texas. contrary to popular belief, not all highways dedicate the left lane as the "fast" lane, as there are some highways that dedicate these left lanes strictly as passing lanes. it is acceptable to use these left lanes for passing, but not to use them continuously for cruising. move off to a lane on the right immediately after you are finished passing a car. such passing lanes are also more common on larger, multi-lane highways. failure to abide by this rule can result in a fine as high as $200 in the state of texas. 3. stay alert for trucks on the highway trucks can sometimes weigh up to 40 tons, and require up to 100 yards to come to a complete stop. one good piece of advice is to keep a safe distance behind trucks by watching when the truck in front of you passes a fixed object, then, seeing if it takes you at least two seconds to pass that same object. if it takes less than two seconds for you to pass that same object, you are driving too closely to that truck. also, don't try to nudge your way between a truck and the curb, as it is a horrendously bad idea. trucks make wide right turns, having several blind spots up to 200 feet behind their trailer, or up to 20 feet in front of the tractor. in other words, they may not see you. a good rule of thumb is that if you can't see the driver's windows or the actual truck driver, then they cannot see you. lastly, never pass a truck from behind when it is in reverse. 4. moving over for emergency vehicles many people naturally move an extra lane away from a stopped emergency vehicle that has bright red flashing lights. this is a correct maneuver, as the law requires you to do this. however, did you know that it is usually also required that you go 20mph below the posted speed limit as you do so? in states such as texas, you could receive a fine of $200 for not following these two rules. tips for road trips and longer drives 5. taking a break being drowsy can be downright deadly when driving on a highway, or anywhere for that matter. driver fatigue is an obvious indication that you are not alert enough to drive safely. if you suddenly find yourself yawning incessantly, drifting unintentionally from lane to lane, or find your eyelids closing intermittently due to tiredness, then pull over to a safe place, and stretch your legs. rest for 15-20 minutes, and repeat this every two hours or so, or better yet, just take a short nap in a safe place, if possible. the best way to combat driver fatigue is to simply prevent it beforehand by preparing yourself. get plenty of rest before a long drive, and avoid any drinking from midnight to 6 o'clock. even tiny amounts of alcohol are enough to influence your reaction time when driving. 6. rest areas are your friend large rest areas are places where you can park your car in a safe environment, and they almost always have law enforcement present. use these places to your advantage as a place of rest, using the bathroom, checking out road conditions, or learning about local points of interest. driving tips highway driving new drivers teen drivers more to explore motorcycle lane spliting on the highway teen driving privileges top riding tips for first-time motorcycle owners teen drinking and driving comments view the discussion thread. save money on car insurance now! enter __label__low cgc events recipes photos cornell gourmet club welcome to the blog of the cornell gourmet club january 13, 2011 digging the pig posted by elliesbelly under main courses leave a comment nine- hour roasted pork shoulder, from the new york times there is something truly magical about pork. whether its in heavenly bacon form or shredded on a sandwich with barbecue sauce, i really dig the pig. and for a chilly place like ithaca, comforting and meltingly tender pork shoulder is just the ticket. its a relatively inexpensive, tough, and somewhat gnarly-looking piece of meat from the shoulder of a pig, and can come with a fat cap on top that is best left on to baste the meat as it cooks. i first tried making pork shoulder, or boston butt as some say, one summer when i had little else to do. my goal was to tackle pulled pork over our little kettle grill but ended up getting impatient with the ten pounds of meat and took it off the heat much too early. my parents smiled politely but i knew it didnt taste right. i looked up more recipes and found that secret to that beautiful meat you can cut with a spoon is a low temperature and a lot of time. i set to work and found new ways to prepare the cut  its adaptable to all kinds of cuisines, and can add a porky punch to soups and stews where it is not necessarily the main attraction. here are a few of my favorites:  swap one inch cubes of pork shoulder for beef in a chili recipe, simmering for 2-2 1/2 hours until tender (yields easily to a fork)  cook the same one inch cubes catalan-style with smoked paprika, green olives, onions and tomatoes until tender for a satisfying winter stew (thanks food and wine mag!)  braise cubes in a thai-style broth with coconut milk, chicken stock, lemongrass, thai curry paste, and lime until tender; serve over rice  pat a 5 to 6 pound cut with barbecue spice rub and cook low and slow in a 225 degree oven for 6 to 7 hours, shredding and serving with barbecue sauce and buns for a crowd  for the nyt roasted pork shoulder in the image above, turn the oven down to 200 and rub a 7 to 8 pound pork shoulder with olive oil, salt, and pepper. roast for 9 to 10 hours until pork can be shredded easily with a fork. serve with salsa verde, recipe at or with a homemade specialty of your own. the above roasted shoulder recipe came from a group dinner held by a cooking school in los angeles, called the pork dinner. thats something i could make the trip for! hopefully, on a cold ithaca weekend a real live pig dinner will be coming to an apartment near you. advertisements share this:emailfacebookprintlike this:like loading... related leave a reply cancel reply enter your comment here... fill in your details below or click an icon to log in: email (required) (address never made public) name (required) website you are commenting using your wordpress.com account.
